{[%evp 0,11,21,13,27,4,39,31,31,26,26,10,-1,-8]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7
4. e4 d6 5. f3 O-O 6. Bg5 {The second most popular move. Nowadays this move is
losing its popularity. The idea of the move is to prevent e7-e5 and also provoke
h7-h6.} a6 $5 {A bit rare, but a very flexible move. The idea is to prepare
c7-c5 and then to be ready after d4-d5 to push b7-b5 immediately.} ({More
popular are the moves:} 6... c5) (6... Nc6) (6... Nbd7) 7. Qd2 {The main move.
All other options are harmless for Black.} (7. Nge2 {This move is quite
typical in Saemish, but in this case, Black is ready for c7-c5 and then the
b7-b5 break.} c5 8. d5 ({The endgame does not look very promising for White.} 
8. dxc5 dxc5 9. Qxd8 Rxd8 10. Na4 {[%csl Rb6,Rc5] Trying to use the weak b6
square.} ({In case of} 10. e5 Nfd7 11. Bxe7 ({Or} 11. Nd5 Nc6) 11... Re8 12.
Nd5 Nc6 {The position becomes very concrete, but somehow it feels like White is
playing with the fire. Next couple of moves are very forced.} 13. Bf6 Ndxe5 14.
Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Nc7 Nd3+ 16. Kd2 Rd8 {[%cal Gd8d2]} 17. Nxa8 Nf2+ 18. Ke3 {
The only way to continue the game.} ({A draw is:} 18. Ke1 Nd3+ $11) 18... Nxh1
19. Nc3 Nb4 {[%cal Gb4c2] The position is very sharp, definitely Black has his
chances.} 20. Rc1 Bf5 21. Nc7 Nc2+ 22. Rxc2 Bxc2 23. g3 h5 $132 {The position
is sharp, but I like Black's chances.}) 10... Nc6 $1 {Black should play very
energetically.} 11. Nec3 ({Or} 11. Nb6 Rb8) (11. Nxc5 Nb4 $1) 11... Nd7 12. Nd5
({In case of} 12. O-O-O {strong is} Bd4 $1 13. Nd5 f6 14. Bf4 Nde5 $132 {
[%csl Gd4,Ge5]}) 12... Kf8 {A simple move.} 13. Rd1 Rb8 14. Bf4 Be5 15. Bxe5
Ncxe5 16. Ndb6 Ke8 17. Nxd7 Nxd7 $11 {Black is out of danger.}) 8... b5 9. cxb5
h6 $1 $146 {An important improvement.} 10. Be3 (10. Bd2 {Looks a bit passive.}
axb5 11. Nxb5 e6 12. dxe6 Bxe6 $132 {[%cal Gd6d5] Black has an excellent
position. d6-d5 is coming next.}) 10... Qa5 11. Qd2 ({Or} 11. Ng3 h5 {[%cal
Gh5h4]} 12. h4 e6 $132) 11... axb5 12. Bxh6 Nbd7 {[%cal Gd7e5]} 13. Ng3 c4 $132
{[%cal Gd7c5,Gb5b4] Black has an excellent counterplay.}) (7. a4 {Without c5/
d5 included this move feels strange.} Nc6 $1 8. Nge2 ({If} 8. d5 $6 {then} Nb4
{[%csl Gb4][%cal Gc7c6] The knight on b4 is untouchable.}) 8... Na5 $1 {
[%csl Rc4]} 9. b3 c6 $132 {[%cal Gd8b6,Ge7e5] Black has excellent prospects.})
(7. Bd3 {It is a strange move, connected with Bg5.} Nfd7 $5 {[%csl Rd4][%cal
Gg7d4] A nice move in this case.} 8. Nge2 c5 9. d5 Ne5 {[%cal Gb7b5] Black has
an excellent play.} 10. a4 {White must prevent b5.} Nbd7 11. b3 ({Worse is:} 
11. f4 $6 Nxd3+ 12. Qxd3 f6 $1 {A very nice and unusual idea. Black already
