Black can play} Bf5 $5 8. Be2 axb4 9. axb4 Rxa1 10. Bxa1 Na6 $1 {when it's not
easy for White to keep his queenside intact.} 11. c3 (11. b5 $2 Nb4 $17 {
[%csl Rc2]}) 11... c6 12. O-O b5 $132 {[%cal Gd8d7,Ga6c7] Black's position is
already more pleasant. He will proceed with ...Nc7 followed by ...Qd7.}) 7...
a4 8. c4 c6 {Black immediately makes use of White's overextended queenside.} 9.
