13. Ne3 Qxc5 $1 {[%cal Gg7c3] The threat of ...Bxc3 is very annoying, White's
position is falling apart.}) 12... e5 {White cannot complete the development.
For example, after} 13. Qe3 {Black has} Rd3 $1) (10. Bg3 Qc7 ({The alternative
} 10... Nd3+ {only makes White's task easier after} 11. Bxd3 Qxd3 12. Nb3) 11.
Qa4 (11. Bxf4 Qxf4) 11... e5 12. Nb3 Nd7 13. Qa5 Qxa5 14. Nxa5 Nxc5 15. O-O-O
Bg4 $11 {The position is dynamically balanced and full of play. 1/2 (102)
Sambuev,B (2541)-Dominguez Perez,L (2739)/chess.com INT 2017/The Week in Chess
1165 (102)}) 10... g5 11. Bg3 ({The immediate} 11. O-O-O {is a bit risky in
